## REPORTING FORMAT

For each finding:
- **Vulnerability**: Name + CWE ID + OWASP category
- **ATT&CK TTP**: Mapped MITRE ATT&CK technique ID and name
- **File & Line**: Exact path and line number
- **Severity**: Critical / High / Medium / Low / Informational
- **CVSS v3 Score**: Estimated base score
- **Exploitability**: How an attacker would exploit this
- **Vulnerable Code**: Exact snippet
- **Fixed Code**: Working remediation example
- **False Positive Assessment**: Likelihood and reasoning

---

## SCAN SCOPE — analyze ALL of the following:

### 1. SECRETS & CREDENTIALS
- Hardcoded API keys, passwords, tokens, private keys
- Base64 encoded secrets
- Secrets in environment variables, .env files, config files
- AWS/GCP/Azure credentials, JWT secrets
- SSH private keys, PEM files
- Database connection strings with credentials

### 2. INJECTION VULNERABILITIES
- SQL injection (raw queries, ORM misuse, second-order SQLi)
- Command injection (os.system, subprocess, shell=True)
- SSTI (template injection in Jinja2, Mako, etc.)
- XXE (XML external entity)
- LDAP injection
- XPath injection
- NoSQL injection (MongoDB, etc.)
- HTTP header injection
- Log injection / log forging
- CRLF injection

### 3. DANGEROUS FUNCTIONS & SINKS
- eval(), exec(), compile()
- pickle, marshal, shelve, yaml.load()
- subprocess with shell=True
- os.system(), os.popen()
- __import__(), importlib misuse
- ctypes, cffi unsafe usage
- open() with user-controlled paths

### 4. AUTHENTICATION & AUTHORIZATION
- Missing authentication on endpoints
- Broken access control / IDOR
- Privilege escalation paths
- JWT: none algorithm, weak secret, missing expiry
- OAuth misconfigurations
- Session fixation / missing session invalidation
- Insecure remember-me tokens
- Mass assignment vulnerabilities

### 5. CRYPTOGRAPHY
- Weak algorithms (MD5, SHA1, DES, RC4, ECB mode)
- Hardcoded IV or salt
- Insecure random (random vs secrets/os.urandom)
- Missing certificate validation (verify=False)
- Weak key sizes
- Improper padding

### 6. INSECURE DESERIALIZATION
- pickle.loads() on untrusted input
- yaml.load() without SafeLoader
- jsonpickle misuse
- Java deserialization equivalents
- XML deserialization

### 7. PATH TRAVERSAL & FILE HANDLING
- User-controlled file paths
- Directory traversal (../)
- Unsafe file uploads (no type/size validation)
- Symlink attacks
- Temp file race conditions (TOCTOU)

### 8. SSRF & NETWORK
- User-controlled URLs in requests
- Internal metadata endpoint exposure (169.254.169.254)
- DNS rebinding risks
- Open redirects
- Unvalidated redirects and forwards

### 9. XSS & CLIENT-SIDE
- Reflected XSS
- Stored XSS
- DOM-based XSS
- Missing Content-Security-Policy
- Dangerous use of innerHTML, document.write

### 10. SENSITIVE DATA EXPOSURE
- PII in logs (names, emails, passwords, tokens)
- Sensitive data in error messages / stack traces
- Debug mode enabled in production
- Verbose error handling exposing internals
- Sensitive data in URLs / query parameters

### 11. RACE CONDITIONS & LOGIC FLAWS
- TOCTOU (time-of-check to time-of-use)
- Threading issues with shared state
- Business logic bypass
- Negative value / integer overflow abuse
- Price or quantity manipulation paths

### 12. DEPENDENCY & SUPPLY CHAIN
- Known vulnerable packages (flag outdated imports)
- Unpinned dependencies
- Typosquatting risk in package names
- Unsafe use of third-party code

### 13. CI/CD & INFRASTRUCTURE
- Secrets in Dockerfile, docker-compose, GitHub Actions YAML
- Privileged container flags
- Exposed ports in configs
- Insecure IaC (Terraform, Ansible, Kubernetes manifests)
- Misconfigured CORS
- Missing security headers

### 14. API SECURITY
- Missing rate limiting
- Unauthenticated API endpoints
- Excessive data exposure in API responses
- GraphQL introspection enabled
- Mass assignment in REST APIs

### 15. MEMORY & RESOURCE
- Unbounded resource consumption (DoS risk)
- Regex DoS (ReDoS) — catastrophic backtracking
- Large file upload without limits
- Infinite loops on user input

